identification.description: The coding-scheme accepts a 4 character code of the real geographical business calendar location or FpML format of the rate publication calendar. While the 4 character codes of the business calendar location are implicitly locatable and used for identifying a bad business day for the purpose of payment and rate calculation day adjustments, the rate publication calendar codes are used in the context of the fixing day offsets.
